would fj work given my home row mods? would it get confused about whether I was doing capital F or capital J? briefly?

Gemini said
It’s a bit risky. In Kanata, combos (like f+j) and home row mods (like @sft_f) can technically coexist, but they often fight over the same "intent."

The Conflict
If you press f and j at the exact same time:

Home Row Mod Logic: Kanata asks, "Are you holding f to shift the next key, or just typing f?"

Combo Logic: Kanata asks, "Did you mean to hit f+j for Escape?"

The Verdict
It won't confuse them for Capital F or J (since those require a third keypress), but it will feel "mushy." You’ll likely see accidental fs or js appearing on your screen when you meant to hit Escape, or you'll accidentally trigger a "Shift" modifier when you just wanted to exit Vim.

Better "Vim-Style" Alternatives
If you want to keep your home row mods clean, try one of these:

The "Dual-Role" Shift: (My favorite) Left Shift = Esc when tapped, Shift when held. No conflict with home row mods.

The jk Combo: Use j+k instead of f+j. Since j and k are both on your right hand, it's a very natural "roll" that rarely misfires during normal typing.

