How it works now:
Physical Left Shift: Tapping it sends Escape (Vim's best friend).

Physical Caps Lock: Acts as Backspace (Your pinky's best friend).

Physical Right Shift: Tapping it toggles Caps Lock. Holding it acts as a standard Right Shift.

One "Vim" Warning
Be careful when using Caps Lock while in Vim! If you toggle it on and forget, your commands like j (down) will suddenly become J (join lines), and i (insert) will become I (insert at start of line).

